{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/polymer-formation/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"고분자polymer\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#%EA%B3%A0%EB%B6%84%EC%9E%90polymer\" aria-label=\"고분자polymer permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>고분자(Polymer)</h2>\n<p>분자의 크기에 따라 분자량이 1,000 이하이면 저분자, 10,000 이상이면 고분자로 분류한다. 고분자는 단량체(monomer)라고 불리는 작은 분자가 수백에서 수천개씩 공유결합으로 연결되어 만들어진다.\n단량체로부터 고분자를 생성하는 반응을 중합(Polymerization)반응이라고 한다.</p>\n<p>고분자는 결국 단량체를 기본으로 하기 때문에, 단량체의 구조에 따라 중합 반응이 다르다. 중합반응은 크게 3가지로 나눌 수 있다.</p>\n<h3 id=\"1-작용기functional-group를-갖는-화합물\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-%EC%9E%91%EC%9A%A9%EA%B8%B0functional-group%EB%A5%BC-%EA%B0%96%EB%8A%94-%ED%99%94%ED%95%A9%EB%AC%BC\" aria-label=\"1 작용기functional group를 갖는 화합물 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. 작용기(functional group)를 갖는 화합물</h3>\n<p>작용기(functional group)는 유기화합물의 화학적 성질을 결정하는 원자단이다.\n예를 들면 아세트산은 <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>–</mtext><mi>C</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{--}COOH</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">–</span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span> 카복시기(Carboxyl Group)를 갖고 있고, 에틸알코올은 <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>–</mtext><mi>O</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{--}OH</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">–</span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span> 하이드록시기(Hydroxy Group)를 갖고 있다.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a52fcaee071186c216717c5d323161ee/f2bd9/image1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 45.39813857290589%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"image1\"\n        title=\"image1\"\n        src=\"/static/a52fcaee071186c216717c5d323161ee/799d3/image1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a52fcaee071186c216717c5d323161ee/00d96/image1.png 148w,\n/static/a52fcaee071186c216717c5d323161ee/0b23c/image1.png 295w,\n/static/a52fcaee071186c216717c5d323161ee/799d3/image1.png 590w,\n/static/a52fcaee071186c216717c5d323161ee/2a3d6/image1.png 885w,\n/static/a52fcaee071186c216717c5d323161ee/f2bd9/image1.png 967w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>1개의 아세트산과 1개의 에틸알콜올을 가열하면, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>–</mtext><mi>C</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>O</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{--}COOH</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">–</span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span> 와 <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mtext>–</mtext><mi>O</mi><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\text{--}OH</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord text\"><span class=\"mord\">–</span></span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.02778em;\">O</span><span class=\"mord mathdefault\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span> 사이의 반응으로 물이 제거되면서 에스테르 화합물인 에틸아세테이트가 생성되며, 반응은 더 이상 진행되지 않고 정지된다.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 590px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9468e7fd7316818d59234a6253cd31be/f2bd9/Polymerization2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 21.199586349534645%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAECAYAAACOXx+WAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAjUlEQVQY03VP7QoDIQzz/Z9SRP+oiIie33ZL4QYbt0KVJmmbCnrHnJP23vQU55yveq31V4sQeLTW1FpjYUqJM8ZIvXcWgfPe0xiDQgjMQYtlwK7rYhx9AmDOmZxzTECAGvjtDs0YDnelFB4IDTBwuBAcfgESDpG3I2BKKR7+e761lrVSSqq1fjhjDC95AZcOOAePvPJbAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Polymerization2\"\n        title=\"Polymerization2\"\n        src=\"/static/9468e7fd7316818d59234a6253cd31be/799d3/Polymerization2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9468e7fd7316818d59234a6253cd31be/00d96/Polymerization2.png 148w,\n/static/9468e7fd7316818d59234a6253cd31be/0b23c/Polymerization2.png 295w,\n/static/9468e7fd7316818d59234a6253cd31be/799d3/Polymerization2.png 590w,\n/static/9468e7fd7316818d59234a6253cd31be/2a3d6/Polymerization2.png 885w,\n/static/9468e7fd7316818d59234a6253cd31be/f2bd9/Polymerization2.png 967w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<center>[화학 반응식]</center>\n<p>이와 같이 두 종류의 단량체로부터 물 등의 간단한 분자가 제거되면서 고분자를 생성하는 반응을 중축합(Polycondensation)이라고 한다. </p>\n<h3 id=\"2-불포화-결합을-갖는-화합물\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-%EB%B6%88%ED%8F%AC%ED%99%94-%EA%B2%B0%ED%95%A9%EC%9D%84-%EA%B0%96%EB%8A%94-%ED%99%94%ED%95%A9%EB%AC%BC\" aria-label=\"2 불포화 결합을 갖는 화합물 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. 불포화 결합을 갖는 화합물</h3>","excerpt":"고분자(Polymer) 분자의 크기에 따라 분자량이 1,000 이하이면 저분자, 10,000 이상이면 고분자로 분류한다. 고분자는 단량체(monomer…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"/polymer-formation/#%EA%B3%A0%EB%B6%84%EC%9E%90polymer\">고분자(Polymer)</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/polymer-formation/#1-%EC%9E%91%EC%9A%A9%EA%B8%B0functional-group%EB%A5%BC-%EA%B0%96%EB%8A%94-%ED%99%94%ED%95%A9%EB%AC%BC\">1. 작용기(functional group)를 갖는 화합물</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/polymer-formation/#2-%EB%B6%88%ED%8F%AC%ED%99%94-%EA%B2%B0%ED%95%A9%EC%9D%84-%EA%B0%96%EB%8A%94-%ED%99%94%ED%95%A9%EB%AC%BC\">2. 불포화 결합을 갖는 화합물</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"slug":"/polymer-formation/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"고분자를 만드는 방법 - 중합반응(Polymerization)","date":"Mar 27, 2020","tags":["Polymer"],"keywords":["Spacebar","jungwoo kim"],"update":"Jan 01, 0001"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/polymer-formation/","series":[],"lastmod":"0001-01-01"}}}